Mitigation.Name: RNGDS_MITG_DIS
Mitigation.SetDescription: SRBDS mitigation is disabled for RDRAND and RDSEED executed outside of Intel SGX enclaves
Mitigation.ClearDescription: SRBDS mitigation is enabled for RDRAND and RDSEED

Mitigation.Name: Indirect Branch Restricted Speculation (IBRS)
Mitigation.SetDescription: The processor restricts speculation of indirect branch
Mitigation.ClearDescription: The processor does not restricts speculation of indirect branch

Mitigation.Name: Single Thread Indirect Branch Predictors (STIBP)
Mitigation.SetDescription: The processor prevents indirect branch predictions on all logical processors on the core from being controlled by any sibling logical processor in the same core
Mitigation.ClearDescription: The processor does not prevents indirect branch predictions on all logical processors on the core from being controlled by any sibling logical processor in the same core

Mitigation.Name: Speculative Store Bypass Disable (SSBD)
Mitigation.SetDescription: The processor delays speculative execution of a load until the addresses of all older stores are known
Mitigation.ClearDescription: The processor does not delays speculative execution of a load until the addresses of all older stores are known

Mitigation.Name: RDCL_NO
Mitigation.SetDescription: The processor is not susceptible to Rogue Data Cache Load (RDCL)
Mitigation.ClearDescription: The processor is susceptible to Rogue Data Cache Load (RDCL)

Mitigation.Name: IBRS_ALL
Mitigation.SetDescription: The processor supports enhanced Indirect Branch Restriction Speculation (IBRS)
Mitigation.ClearDescription: The processor does not supports enhanced Indirect Branch Restriction Speculation (IBRS)

Mitigation.Name: RSBA
Mitigation.SetDescription: The processor supports RSB Alternate. Alternative branch predictors may be used by RET instructions when the RSB is empty. Software using retpoline may be affected by this behavior
Mitigation.ClearDescription: The processor does not supports RSB Alternate. Alternative branch predictors may be used by RET instructions when the RSB is empty. Software using retpoline may be affected by this behavior

Mitigation.Name: SKIP_L1DFL_VMENTRY
Mitigation.SetDescription: A value of 1 indicates the hypervisor need not flush the L1D on VM entry
Mitigation.ClearDescription: A value of 0 indicates the hypervisor need to flush the L1D on VM entry

Mitigation.Name: SSB_NO
Mitigation.SetDescription: The processor is not susceptible to Speculative Store Bypass (SSB)
Mitigation.ClearDescription: The processor is susceptible to Speculative Store Bypass (SSB)

Mitigation.Name: MDS_NO
Mitigation.SetDescription: The processor is not susceptible to Microarchitectural Data Sampling (MDS)
Mitigation.ClearDescription: The processor is susceptible to Microarchitectural Data Sampling (MDS)

Mitigation.Name: MFBDS
Mitigation.SetDescription: The processor is not affected by MFBDS/MSBDS/MLPDS/MDSUM. MFBDS is mitigated if either the RDCL_NO or MDS_NO bit (or both) are set.
Mitigation.ClearDescription: The processor is affected by MFBDS/MSBDS/MLPDS/MDSUM. MFBDS is mitigated if either the RDCL_NO or MDS_NO bit (or both) are set.

Mitigation.Name: IF_PSCHANGE_MC_NO
Mitigation.SetDescription: The processor is not susceptible to a machine check error due to modifying the size of a code page without TLB invalidation
Mitigation.ClearDescription: The processor is susceptible to a machine check error due to modifying the size of a code page without TLB invalidation

Mitigation.Name: TSX_CTRL
Mitigation.SetDescription: The processor supports RTM_DISABLE and TSX_CPUID_CLEAR
Mitigation.ClearDescription: The processor does not supports RTM_DISABLE and TSX_CPUID_CLEAR

Mitigation.Name: TAA_NO
Mitigation.SetDescription: The processor is not susceptible to Intel速 Transactional Synchronization Extensions (Intel速 TSX) Asynchronous Abort (TAA)
Mitigation.ClearDescription: The processor is susceptible to Intel速 Transactional Synchronization Extensions (Intel速 TSX) Asynchronous Abort (TAA)

Mitigation.Name: MCU_CONTROL
Mitigation.SetDescription: The processor support MCU Lock-Out MSR IA32_MCU_CONTROL
Mitigation.ClearDescription: The processor does not support MCU Lock-Out MSR IA32_MCU_CONTROL

Mitigation.Name: IA32_MISC_PACKAGE_CTLS
Mitigation.SetDescription: The processor support IA32_MISC_PACKAGE_CTLS MSR (MSR 0xBC)
Mitigation.ClearDescription: The processor does not support IA32_MISC_PACKAGE_CTLS MSR (MSR 0xBC)

Mitigation.Name: ENERGY_FILTERING_ENABLE
Mitigation.SetDescription: The processor have energy filtering mitigation enabled
Mitigation.ClearDescription: The processor does not have energy filtering mitigation enabled

Mitigation.Name: SBDR_SSDP_NO

Mitigation.ClearDescription: The processor is affected by either the Shared Buffers Data Read (SBDR) vulnerability or the Sideband Stale Data Propagator (SSDP) propagator

Mitigation.Name: FBSDP_NO
Mitigation.SetDescription: The processor is not affected by the Fill Buffer Stale Data Propagator (FBSDP) propagator
Mitigation.ClearDescription: The processor is affected by the Fill Buffer Stale Data Propagator (FBSDP) propagator

Mitigation.Name: PSDP_NO
Mitigation.SetDescription: The processor is not affected by vulnerabilities involving Primary Stale Data Propagator (PSDP) propagator
Mitigation.ClearDescription: The processor is affected by vulnerabilities involving Primary Stale Data Propagator (PSDP) propagator

Mitigation.Name: FB_CLEAR
Mitigation.SetDescription: The processor will overwrite fill buffer values when MD_CLEAR is executed. This property is also true for processors that enumerate support for both L1D_FLUSH[1] and MD_CLEAR[2]; even if IA32_ARCH_CAPABILITIES.FB_CLEAR is 0
Mitigation.ClearDescription: The processor will not overwrite fill buffer values when MD_CLEAR is executed. This property is also true for processors that enumerate support for both L1D_FLUSH[1] and MD_CLEAR[2]; even if IA32_ARCH_CAPABILITIES.FB_CLEAR is 0

Mitigation.Name: FB_CLEAR_CTRL
Mitigation.SetDescription: The processor support read and write to TBD MSR (MSR address TBD) and to the FB_CLEAR_DIS bit in that MSR (bit position TBD). On such processors, the FB_CLEAR_DIS bit can be set to cause the VERW instruction to not perform the MD_CLEAR action
Mitigation.ClearDescription: The processor does not support read and write to TBD MSR (MSR address TBD) and to the FB_CLEAR_DIS bit in that MSR (bit position TBD). On such processors, the FB_CLEAR_DIS bit can be set to cause the VERW instruction to not perform the MD_CLEAR action
